rComments: Class is relatively easy. Lectures aren't filled with a lot of content and clicker questions are helpful for learning main concepts.

This semester he said he redid the way the course was taught & the style of the exams, and nearly everyone had an A or a B. Class was usually interesting. Sometimes uses too many clicker q's to the point where an entire lecture is based on them. The material generally isn't difficult but studying is necessary.

Very boring class. You feel like you learn nothing. The last fourth of the material is a total waste, confusing, and need to relearn in a more organized setting before being able to apply it to anything. He seems nice, but not very well-informed about what he was teaching.

Seems afraid to lecture in front of students and gets easily confused.The class is unorganized,and very frustrating at times(not from being hard,material seems remedial),but if you read the book&review the lecture slides you will do fine despite him not being the best.80% of the class got an A or B.You will leave feeling you didn't learn much.
Worst class ever. drop class before its too late. Confusing professors. Boring topics. Awful labs. terrible TAs
He thoroughly confused half the class regarding alternation of generations...including himself.

People complained because his tests required application of concepts rather than just definitions, but I enjoyed his class because he used lots of current examples to teach concepts and keep students interested.
Marcot teaches like he's too good for a 100 level class and takes pride in failing students. Nice work!
